<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1831,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1831,1856]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[305,572,1831,1856]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">
<typeStatus box="[305,416,1831,1856]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">Holotype</typeStatus>
. Adult male.
</emphasis>
Structure typical for 
<taxonomicName box="[820,965,1831,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[820,965,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">Ochrotrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<bibRefCitation author="Flint" box="[1036,1157,1831,1856]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" refString="Flint, O. S. Jr. (1972) Studies of Neotropical Caddisflies, XIII: The Genus Ochrotrichia from Mexico and Central America (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 118, 1 - 28. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.118" type="journal article" year="1972">
Flint 
<number box="[1100,1157,1832,1856]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) except body length 2.0 mm (from tip of head to end of the folded wing). Length of each forewing 
<quantity box="[1003,1093,1868,1892]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
. General color uniform brown (in alcohol). Head without modification. Tibial spur formula: 
<number box="[886,921,1904,1928]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1-3</number>
- 
<number box="[931,949,1904,1928]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" value="4.0">4</number>
. Metascutellum subpentagonal. Abdomen without visible modifications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1831,2036]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,645]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">
Male genitalia. Sternum IX with anterior portion excavated in lateral view; anterior margin rounded; posterior margin truncate (
<figureCitation box="[341,476,2011,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[293,1292,710,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[279,1308,697,1926]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Ochrotrichia igrapiuna sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229021/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">
Fig. 
<number box="[393,407,2011,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" value="5.0">5</number>
A, 
<number box="[441,455,2011,2036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" value="5.0">5</number>
C
</figureCitation>
); tergum IX very short forming a short transverse bar in dorsal view; posterior margin darker (
<figureCitation box="[238,327,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[293,1292,710,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[279,1308,697,1926]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Ochrotrichia igrapiuna sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229021/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[292,307,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" value="5.0">5</number>
B
</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages long; rectangular in lateral view with apex slightly truncate (
<figureCitation box="[1265,1353,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[293,1292,710,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[279,1308,697,1926]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Ochrotrichia igrapiuna sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229021/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[1318,1332,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" value="5.0">5</number>
C
</figureCitation>
); distal portion slightly curved inwards and tapering in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[846,937,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[293,1292,710,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[279,1308,697,1926]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Ochrotrichia igrapiuna sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229021/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[899,913,188,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" value="5.0">5</number>
A
</figureCitation>
); with long setae over all surface and spinelike setae on internal surface (
<figureCitation box="[489,627,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[293,1292,710,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[279,1308,697,1926]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Ochrotrichia igrapiuna sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229021/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[542,556,223,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" value="5.0">5</number>
A, 
<number box="[590,604,223,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" value="5.0">5</number>
C
</figureCitation>
). Segment X tergum elongate and not divided; triangular in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[159,248,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[293,1292,710,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[279,1308,697,1926]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Ochrotrichia igrapiuna sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229021/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[213,227,260,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" value="5.0">5</number>
C
</figureCitation>
); with a basal sclerotized, spine-like process on the left side in dorsal view; mesal area with an enlarged and darker area on the right side (
<figureCitation box="[534,623,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[293,1292,710,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[279,1308,697,1926]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Ochrotrichia igrapiuna sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229021/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[587,602,295,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" value="5.0">5</number>
B
</figureCitation>
). Phallus tubular, very slender, and tapering to apex; without processes; ejaculatory duct not protruding (
<figureCitation box="[514,603,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 A – D" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[293,1292,710,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[279,1308,697,1926]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5 A – D. Ochrotrichia igrapiuna sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229021/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
Fig. 
<number box="[566,580,332,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" value="5.0">5</number>
D
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,645]" box="[199,511,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Female and larva unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="280" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,404,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[327,595,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igrapiuna" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[327,595,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Ochrotrichia igrapiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[607,702,404,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[607,702,404,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is tentatively placed in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1042,1135,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xena">
<emphasis box="[1042,1135,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">O. xena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group due to the overall arrangement of the genitalia, in which tergum X is a simple flap sometimes bearing a few spines. This is a very distinctive 
<taxonomicName box="[274,419,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,419,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Ochrotrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species and can be easily distinguished by the triangular shape of tergum X in lateral view and enlarged and darker area on its right side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="280" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species name alludes to the 
<typeStatus box="[714,762,549,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">type</typeStatus>
locality. The origin of the municipality name is not certain, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,258,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="igrapiuna" status="sp. nov.">Igrapiúna</taxonomicName>
either is derived from 
<emphasis box="[537,676,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="280">ygara-piuna</emphasis>
(meaning “black canoe” in Tupi language) or from ygarapé-una (meaning “small stream with black water” in Tupi-guarani language).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
